31struct dns_dns64 {
32 unsigned char bits[16]; /*
33 * Prefix + suffix bits.
34 */
35 dns_acl_t * clients; /*
36 * Which clients get mapped
37 * addresses.
38 */
39 dns_acl_t * mapped; /*
40 * IPv4 addresses to be mapped.
41 */
42 dns_acl_t * excluded; /*
43 * IPv6 addresses that are
44 * treated as not existing.
45 */
46 unsigned int prefixlen; /*
47 * Start of mapped address.
48 */
49 unsigned int flags;
50 isc_mem_t * mctx;
51 ISC_LINK(dns_dns64_t) link;
52};
53
54isc_result_t
55dns_dns64_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, const isc_netaddr_t *prefix,
56 unsigned int prefixlen, const isc_netaddr_t *suffix,
57 dns_acl_t *clients, dns_acl_t *mapped, dns_acl_t *excluded,
58 unsigned int flags, dns_dns64_t **dns64p)
59{
60 dns_dns64_t *dns64;
61 unsigned int nbytes = 16;
62
63 REQUIRE(prefix != NULL && prefix->family == AF_INET6);
64 /* Legal prefix lengths from rfc6052.txt. */
65 REQUIRE(prefixlen == 32 || prefixlen == 40 || prefixlen == 48 ||
66 prefixlen == 56 || prefixlen == 64 || prefixlen == 96);
67 REQUIRE(isc_netaddr_prefixok(prefix, prefixlen) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
68 REQUIRE(dns64p != NULL && *dns64p == NULL);
69
70 if (suffix != NULL) {
71 static const unsigned char zeros[16];
72 REQUIRE(prefix->family == AF_INET6);
73 nbytes = prefixlen / 8 + 4;
74 /* Bits 64-71 are zeros. rfc6052.txt */
75 if (prefixlen >= 32 && prefixlen <= 64)
76 nbytes++;
77 REQUIRE(memcmp(suffix->type.in6.s6_addr, zeros, nbytes) == 0);
78 }
79
80 dns64 = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(dns_dns64_t));
81 if (dns64 == NULL)
82 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
83 memset(dns64->bits, 0, sizeof(dns64->bits));
84 memmove(dns64->bits, prefix->type.in6.s6_addr, prefixlen / 8);
85 if (suffix != NULL)
86 memmove(dns64->bits + nbytes, suffix->type.in6.s6_addr + nbytes,
87 16 - nbytes);
88 dns64->clients = NULL;
89 if (clients != NULL)
90 dns_acl_attach(clients, &dns64->clients);
91 dns64->mapped = NULL;
92 if (mapped != NULL)
93 dns_acl_attach(mapped, &dns64->mapped);
94 dns64->excluded = NULL;
95 if (excluded != NULL)
96 dns_acl_attach(excluded, &dns64->excluded);
97 dns64->prefixlen = prefixlen;
98 dns64->flags = flags;
99 ISC_LINK_INIT(dns64, link);
100 dns64->mctx = NULL;
101 isc_mem_attach(mctx, &dns64->mctx);
102 *dns64p = dns64;
103 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
104}
105
106void
107dns_dns64_destroy(dns_dns64_t **dns64p) {
108 dns_dns64_t *dns64;
109
110 REQUIRE(dns64p != NULL && *dns64p != NULL);
111
112 dns64 = *dns64p;
113 *dns64p = NULL;
114
115 REQUIRE(!ISC_LINK_LINKED(dns64, link));
116
117 if (dns64->clients != NULL)
118 dns_acl_detach(&dns64->clients);
119 if (dns64->mapped != NULL)
120 dns_acl_detach(&dns64->mapped);
121 if (dns64->excluded != NULL)
122 dns_acl_detach(&dns64->excluded);
123 isc_mem_putanddetach(&dns64->mctx, dns64, sizeof(*dns64));
124}

126isc_result_t
127dns_dns64_aaaafroma(const dns_dns64_t *dns64, const isc_netaddr_t *reqaddr,
128 const dns_name_t *reqsigner, const dns_aclenv_t *env,
129 unsigned int flags, unsigned char *a, unsigned char *aaaa)
130{
131 unsigned int nbytes, i;
132 isc_result_t result;
133 int match;
134
135 if ((dns64->flags & DNS_DNS64_RECURSIVE_ONLY) != 0 &&
136 (flags & DNS_DNS64_RECURSIVE) == 0)
137 return (DNS_R_DISALLOWED);
138
139 if ((dns64->flags & DNS_DNS64_BREAK_DNSSEC) == 0 &&
140 (flags & DNS_DNS64_DNSSEC) != 0)
141 return (DNS_R_DISALLOWED);
142
143 if (dns64->clients != NULL) {
144 result = dns_acl_match(reqaddr, reqsigner, dns64->clients,
145 env, &match, NULL);
146 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
147 return (result);
148 if (match <= 0)
149 return (DNS_R_DISALLOWED);
150 }
151
152 if (dns64->mapped != NULL) {
153 struct in_addr ina;
154 isc_netaddr_t netaddr;
155
156 memmove(&ina.s_addr, a, 4);
157 isc_netaddr_fromin(&netaddr, &ina);
158 result = dns_acl_match(&netaddr, NULL, dns64->mapped,
159 env, &match, NULL);
160 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
161 return (result);
162 if (match <= 0)
163 return (DNS_R_DISALLOWED);
164 }
165
166 nbytes = dns64->prefixlen / 8;
167 INSIST(nbytes <= 12);
168 /* Copy prefix. */
169 memmove(aaaa, dns64->bits, nbytes);
170 /* Bits 64-71 are zeros. rfc6052.txt */
171 if (nbytes == 8)
172 aaaa[nbytes++] = 0;
173 /* Copy mapped address. */
174 for (i = 0; i < 4U; i++) {
175 aaaa[nbytes++] = a[i];
176 /* Bits 64-71 are zeros. rfc6052.txt */
177 if (nbytes == 8)
178 aaaa[nbytes++] = 0;
179 }
180 /* Copy suffix. */
181 memmove(aaaa + nbytes, dns64->bits + nbytes, 16 - nbytes);
182 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
183}
184
185dns_dns64_t *
186dns_dns64_next(dns_dns64_t *dns64) {
187 dns64 = ISC_LIST_NEXT(dns64, link);
188 return (dns64);
189}

191void
192dns_dns64_append(dns_dns64list_t *list, dns_dns64_t *dns64) {
193 ISC_LIST_APPEND(*list, dns64, link);
194}

196void
197dns_dns64_unlink(dns_dns64list_t *list, dns_dns64_t *dns64) {
198 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(*list, dns64, link);
199}

201bool
202dns_dns64_aaaaok(const dns_dns64_t *dns64, const isc_netaddr_t *reqaddr,
203 const dns_name_t *reqsigner, const dns_aclenv_t *env,
204 unsigned int flags, dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
205 bool *aaaaok, size_t aaaaoklen)
206{
207 struct in6_addr in6;
208 isc_netaddr_t netaddr;
209 isc_result_t result;
210 int match;
211 bool answer = false;
212 bool found = false;
213 unsigned int i, ok;
214
215 REQUIRE(rdataset != NULL);
216 REQUIRE(rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_aaaa);
217 REQUIRE(rdataset->rdclass == dns_rdataclass_in);
218 if (aaaaok != NULL)
219 REQUIRE(aaaaoklen == dns_rdataset_count(rdataset));
220
221 for (;dns64 != NULL; dns64 = ISC_LIST_NEXT(dns64, link)) {
222 if ((dns64->flags & DNS_DNS64_RECURSIVE_ONLY) != 0 &&
223 (flags & DNS_DNS64_RECURSIVE) == 0)
224 continue;
225
226 if ((dns64->flags & DNS_DNS64_BREAK_DNSSEC) == 0 &&
227 (flags & DNS_DNS64_DNSSEC) != 0)
228 continue;
229 /*
230 * Work out if this dns64 structure applies to this client.
231 */
232 if (dns64->clients != NULL) {
233 result = dns_acl_match(reqaddr, reqsigner,
234 dns64->clients, env,
235 &match, NULL);
236 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
237 continue;
238 if (match <= 0)
239 continue;
240 }
241
242 if (!found && aaaaok != NULL) {
243 for (i = 0; i < aaaaoklen; i++)
244 aaaaok[i] = false;
245 }
246 found = true;
247
248 /*
249 * If we are not excluding any addresses then any AAAA
250 * will do.
251 */
252 if (dns64->excluded == NULL) {
253 answer = true;
254 if (aaaaok == NULL)
255 goto done;
256 for (i = 0; i < aaaaoklen; i++)
257 aaaaok[i] = true;
258 goto done;
259 }
260
261 i = 0; ok = 0;
262 for (result = dns_rdataset_first(rdataset);
263 result == ISC_R_SUCCESS;
264 result = dns_rdataset_next(rdataset)) {
265 dns_rdata_t rdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
266 if (aaaaok == NULL || !aaaaok[i]) {
267
268 dns_rdataset_current(rdataset, &rdata);
269 memmove(&in6.s6_addr, rdata.data, 16);
270 isc_netaddr_fromin6(&netaddr, &in6);
271
272 result = dns_acl_match(&netaddr, NULL,
273 dns64->excluded, env,
274 &match, NULL);
275 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && match <= 0) {
276 answer = true;
277 if (aaaaok == NULL)
278 goto done;
279 aaaaok[i] = true;
280 ok++;
281 }
282 } else
283 ok++;
284 i++;
285 }
286 /*
287 * Are all addresses ok?
288 */
289 if (aaaaok != NULL && ok == aaaaoklen)
290 goto done;
291 }
292
293 done:
294 if (!found && aaaaok != NULL) {
295 for (i = 0; i < aaaaoklen; i++)
296 aaaaok[i] = true;
297 }
298 return (found ? answer : true);
299}
